  "prompt": "How should I fill my first name and last name in a form, when I have my surname as first name in India?",
  "response": "In India, many people have their surname or family name as their first name, which can create confusion when filling out forms designed with Western naming conventions. Here are some tips:\n\n1. Check the form's instructions:\n- Some forms have specific guidelines for Indian names\n- Look for instructions about name order or cultural variations\n\n2. Contact the form issuer:\n- Ask for clarification on how to fill out the name fields\n- They may provide guidance specific to their form\n\n3. General strategies:\n- If possible, swap the name order\n- Place your surname in the \"Last Name\" field\n- Put your given name in the \"First Name\" field\n\n4. If swapping isn't possible:\n- Enter your full name in the \"First Name\" field\n- Leave the \"Last Name\" field blank or repeat the surname\n- Add a note explaining your naming convention if there's space\n\n5. Consistency is key:\n- Use the same name format across different documents\n- Match the name order on your official identification documents\n\n6. When in doubt:\n- Consult with the organization requesting the form\n- Seek advice from someone familiar with the specific form or process\n\nRemember, practices can vary depending on the specific form and organization.",
